      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RANGER'S GIRL (1) goes very well at the course and distance with three wins and a placing from eight starts. Was out of the placings last time (26.97) at Warragul in a Grade 5, finishing seventh and beaten 7 lengths. Expected to go close. WESTERN FEEL (2) box seated early before forging to the lead turning and lifting to score (25.05) at Sale in a Grade 5 over 435m. Shapes as a top winning chance on latest effort. TILES AND WINE (7) turned in a better effort at Sale last start, finishing second behind WESTERN FEEL (25.15) in a Grade 5. Has the pace to be prominent. Expected to be in this for a long way. OUR MATE BEAR (6) is worth some thought after placing last start.",
